How can I generate a random matrix with dimensions 4x4 and values ranging from 1 to 10, and then find the transpose of the matrix using JavaScript code? Please provide the JavaScript code in [JavaScript code] format below.
Additionally, please include the resulting matrix and its transpose in [JavaScript code] format as input data in the rewritten prompt:
Input data:
Original Matrix:
[[2, 8, 7, 10], [9, 10, 1, 6], [1, 5, 7, 6], [8, 5, 4, 9]]
Transpose Matrix:
[[2, 9, 1, 8], [8, 10, 5, 5], [7, 1, 7, 4], [10, 6, 6, 9]]
JavaScript code:
let matrix = [];
for (let i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
  matrix[i] = [];
  for (let j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
    matrix[i][j] = Math.floor(Math.random() * 10) + 1;
  }
}
let transpose_matrix = matrix[0].map((col, i) => matrix.map(row => row[i]));
console.log("Original Matrix: ");
console.log(matrix);
console.log("Transpose Matrix: ");
console.log(transpose_matrix);

Certainly! Below is the JavaScript code that generates a random 4x4 matrix with values ranging from 1 to 10, and then calculates its transpose. The given input data includes an example of an original matrix and its transpose. 

```[JavaScript code]
let matrix = [];
for (let i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
  matrix[i] = [];
  for (let j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
    matrix[i][j] = Math.floor(Math.random() * 10) + 1;
  }
}

let transpose_matrix = matrix[0].map((col, i) => matrix.map(row => row[i]));

console.log("Original Matrix: ");
console.log(matrix);
console.log("Transpose Matrix: ");
console.log(transpose_matrix);
```

Here's the example input data:

```[JavaScript code]
Input data:
Original Matrix:
[[2, 8, 7, 10], [9, 10, 1, 6], [1, 5, 7, 6], [8, 5, 4, 9]]
Transpose Matrix:
[[2, 9, 1, 8], [8, 10, 5, 5], [7, 1, 7, 4], [10, 6, 6, 9]]
```

This script will create a new random matrix and its transpose each time it's run, so you'll see different values in the console output.
